cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a deep learning based detector for 2D range data, specifically for detecting wheelchairs and walkers. This falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (cs.LG) and proposes a depth preprocessing step and voting scheme (cs.AI) to improve performance. Additionally, the paper mentions the potential loss of performance due to suboptimal design choices, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
